wxString CSharedFileList::GetPublicSharedDirName ( const CPath &  dir  ) 

Returns the name of a folder visible to the public.

Parameters:
dir The full path to a shared directory.
Returns:
The name of the shared directory that will be visible to the public.

This function is used to hide sensitive data considering the directory structure of the client. The returned public name consists of only subdirectories that are shared. Example: /ed2k/shared/games/tetris -> "games/tetris" if /ed2k/shared are not marked as shared

References CPath::GetPrintable(), CPath::GetRaw(), and IsShared().
